# Documentation File Management

## CRITICAL REQUIREMENT
**All generated .md files must be added to .gitignore** to prevent documentation clutter in the repository.

## Required .gitignore Entries

The following patterns MUST be added to [.gitignore](mdc:.gitignore):

```gitignore
# Generated documentation files
*.md
!README.md
!CLERK_SETUP.md
!docs/**/*.md

# Cursor-generated files
cursor-*.md
app-description*.md
project-overview*.md
```

## Documentation Management Rules

### ✅ ALLOWED Documentation Files
- `README.md` - Main project documentation
- `CLERK_SETUP.md` - Setup instructions
- Files in `docs/` directory - Organized documentation
- Files explicitly committed by developers

### ❌ FORBIDDEN in Repository
- Auto-generated .md files from Cursor
- Temporary documentation files
- AI-generated app descriptions
- Project overview files created during development

## Implementation Requirements

### Immediate Actions Required
1. Add the gitignore patterns above to `.gitignore`
2. Remove any existing auto-generated .md files from tracking
3. Commit the updated `.gitignore` file

### Ongoing Maintenance
- Review any new .md files before committing
- Ensure generated documentation stays in `docs/` directory
- Use meaningful names for permanent documentation

## File Organization Standards

### Permanent Documentation Structure
```
docs/
  ├── setup/           # Setup and installation guides
  ├── api/             # API documentation  
  ├── features/        # Feature documentation
  └── development/     # Development guides
```

### Temporary Files (Auto-Ignored)
- Any .md files in root directory (except exceptions)
- Files matching cursor-*.md pattern
- Files matching app-description*.md pattern

## Anti-Patterns to Avoid

### ❌ Repository Pollution
```
# Don't commit these types of files
app-description-2024-12-14.md
cursor-generated-overview.md
project-summary.md
feature-list.md
```

### ❌ Inconsistent Documentation
- Don't mix auto-generated and manual documentation
- Don't commit temporary documentation files
- Don't bypass the gitignore for convenience

## Enforcement Checklist

For every commit:
- [ ] Check no auto-generated .md files are staged
- [ ] Verify .gitignore patterns are working
- [ ] Ensure permanent docs are in proper directories
- [ ] Review any new documentation for appropriateness

This rule ensures clean repository management while preserving important project documentation.